{
  format: 1
  name: combinators-lack-precedence-and-grouping-invalid
  suite: static
  tags: [grammar, combinators, precedence, adversarial]
  // Pedantic-implementer probe: chain three view combinators of different kinds
  // where the grouping changes the result. '.a | .b & .c' evaluates to
  // '(.a | .b) & .c' or '.a | (.b & .c)' with different membership, projection,
  // and identity (§7.4). SPEC-ISSUES #25 (pinned): `|` and `&` share ONE
  // precedence level; a chain repeating one combinator (a|b|c) is left-
  // associative, but a chain MIXING `|` and `&` is a static error the author must
  // disambiguate with `( )` grouping (CEL syntax, §6.1) — e.g. `(a | b) & c` or
  // `a | (b & c)`. So the un-parenthesized mixed chain below is rejected at load.
  note: "SPEC-ISSUES #25: `|` and `&` share one precedence level; a chain mixing them without `( )` grouping is ambiguous (the groupings differ in order/projection/identity, §7.4) and is a static load error. A repeated single combinator stays left-associative; grouping uses `( )` (§6.1)."
  spec: ["#annex-c", "§C.8", "#views", "§7.4"]

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.combprec@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      items: {
        $key: "id"
        id: "text"
        a: "bool"
        b: "bool"
        c: "bool"
      }
      mixed: {
        $view: ".items[:i | i.a] { id } | .items[:i | i.b] { id } & .items[:i | i.c] { id }"
      }
      $public: {
        items: { $view: ".mixed" }
      }
    }
  }

  expect: {
    outcome: invalid
    violates: ["#annex-c", "§C.8", "#views", "§7.4"]
    detail: "the view `.items[a] { id } | .items[b] { id } & .items[c] { id }` mixes `|` and `&` without `( )` grouping; the ambiguous chain is rejected"
  }
}
